This '''glossary of ecology''' is a list of definitions of terms and topics in [[ecology]] and related fields. For more specific definitions from other glossaries related to ecology, see [[Glossary of biology]] and [[Glossary of environmental science]].

{{compact ToC|side=yes|center=yes|nobreak=yes|seealso=yes|refs=yes|extlinks=yes|}}

{{Science}}

==A==

{{glossary}}
{{term|term= '''[[abiotic component]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= }}

{{term|term= '''[[adaptive behavior (ecology)|adaptive behavior]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= In [[#behavioral ecology|behavioral ecology]], any behavior which contributes to an individual's [[sexual reproduction|reproductive]] success and is thus subject to the forces of [[natural selection]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[atmosphere of Earth|air]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= See [[#atmosphere|atmosphere]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[allee effect]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A concept in [[#population ecology|population ecology]] that describes the positive relationship between the size of a given population and its growth.}}

{{term|term= '''[[animals|animal]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= }}

{{term|term= '''[[ethology|animal behaviour]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= See [[#ethology|ethology]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[animal communication]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= }}

{{term|term= '''[[animal migration]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= }}

{{term|term= '''[[applied ecology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A branch of ecology which uses ecological principles and insights to solve environment-related problems. It includes [[#agroecology|agroecology]] and [[#conservation biology|conservation biology]].}}

<span id="aquatic plant"></span>{{term|term= '''[[aquatic plant]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A [[vascular plant]] adapted to living in [[saline water|salt water]] or [[fresh water]] aquatic environments.}}

{{term|term= '''[[island biogeography|area effect]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The [[biogeography|biogeographic]] hypothesis that larger islands are able to support more species than smaller ones.}}

{{term|term= '''[[Earth's atmosphere|atmosphere]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Earth's atmosphere is composed of gases and water which are retained by Earth's [[gravity]] and help to [[greenhouse effect|retain heat]] and reflect [[UV radiation]].}}

<span id="autecology"></span>{{term|term= '''[[population ecology|autecology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A major sub-field of ecology which studies the dynamics of populations and the ways in which they interact with the environment. Also called ''[[#population ecology|population ecology]]''.}}

{{term|term= '''[[autopoïesis]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= }}

{{term|term= '''[[autotroph]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= See [[#producer|producer]].}}

