{{glossary}}
{{term|term= '''[[bacteria]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= }}

<span id="behavioral ecology"></span>{{term|term= '''[[behavioral ecology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A branch of ecology which studies the ecological and [[evolution]]ary basis of [[animal behavior]], mainly at the level of the individual.}}

{{term|term= '''[[benthos]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= }}

{{term|term= '''[[biodegradable]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Capable of decaying through the action of living organisms.}}

<span id="biodiversity"></span>{{term|term= '''[[biodiversity]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Diversity among and within plant and animal species in a given environment.}}

{{term|term= '''[[biogeochemistry]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The science that studies the effects of [[biota (ecology)|biota]] on global chemistry and on the cycles of matter and energy that transport Earth's chemical components in time and space.}}

<span id="biogeochemical cycle"></span>{{term|term= '''[[biogeochemical cycle]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A pathway through which a [[chemical element]] or [[molecule]] moves through the [[atmosphere]], [[hydrosphere]], [[lithosphere]], and [[biosphere]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[biogeographic realm]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= See [[#ecozone|ecozone]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[biogeography]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= the study of the [[geography|geographic]] [[species distribution|distribution]] of species on Earth.}}

{{term|term= '''[[Bioinvader|bio-invader]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A non-native species.}}

{{term|term= '''[[biological dispersal]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The movement of organisms from their birth site to their breeding site or from one breeding site to another.}}

{{term|term= '''[[biological magnification]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The increase in concentration of a [[chemical substance]] in the [[tissue (biology)|tissues]] of organisms comprising successively higher levels in a [[food chain]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[biological organization]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= }}

{{term|term= '''[[biomass (ecology)|biomass]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The sum of all living organisms in a given area.}}

{{term|term= '''[[biomass pyramid]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A graph that illustrates the productivity within a [[trophic level]] Also called an ''[[ecological pyramid]]''.}}

<span id="biome"></span>{{term|term= '''[[biome]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The total complex of [[biocoenosis|biotic communities]] occupying and characterizing a particular area.}}

{{term|term= '''[[biosphere]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The global sum of all ecosystems on Earth.}}

{{term|term= '''[[biota (ecology)|biota]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The total collection of organisms of a [[geographic region]] or a time period.}}

{{term|term= '''[[biotic component]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= }}

{{term|term= '''[[biotic potential]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The maximum achievable rate of increase of a population in a given area under ideal conditions.}}

{{term|term= '''[[boreal forest]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Forest areas of the northern [[temperate zone]], mostly consisting of [[conifer]]s. Also called  [[taiga]] in [[Siberia]].}}

