==D==

{{glossary}}
{{term|term= '''[[temperate deciduous forest|deciduous broadleaf forest]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Any forest situated in a [[temperate zone]] whose trees shed their leaves during the [[winter|cold season]].}}

<span id="decomposer"></span>{{term|term= '''[[decomposer]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Any organism that [[biodegradation|breaks down]] decomposing bits of [[organic matter]].}}

<span id="decomposition"></span>{{term|term= '''[[decomposition]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The process by which [[tissue (biology)|tissues]] of dead organisms break down into simpler forms of [[organic matter]], thereby clearing the limited available space in a [[#biome|biome]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[deep sea community]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Any [[community (ecology)|community]] of organisms linked by a shared habitat in the [[deep sea]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[deforestation]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= }}

<span id="denitrification"></span>{{term|term= '''[[denitrification]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The breakdown of [[nitrate]]s (mostly in the soil), by [[anaerobic digestion|anaerobic]] [[bacteria]], into their constituent [[chemical elements]]: [[nitrogen]] and [[oxygen]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[density dependence]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The dependence of the growth rate of a population of a given species on its [[population density|density]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[desert]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A landscape that receives less than 10 inches of [[rain]] per year.}}

{{term|term= '''[[desert ecology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The sum of interactions between both [[biotic component|biotic]] and [[abiotic]] factors that occur in a desert [[biome]], including interactions between plant, animal, and [[bacteria]]l populations in a desert [[community (ecology)|community]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[desertification]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A process by which areas become desert-like wastelands with a lower, and different [[biodiversity]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[detrital food web]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A food web depicting the energy flow from [[photoautotrophs]] through [[detritivore]]s and decomposers.}}

{{term|term= '''[[detritivore]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= [[Heterotroph]]s which [[biodegradation|consume]] decomposing bits of [[organic matter]], such as [[plant litter]].}}

<span id="disturbance"></span>{{term|term= '''[[disturbance (ecology)|disturbance]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= }}

{{term|term= '''[[dominance hierarchy]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The organization of individual organisms into groups with a social structure.}}

{{term|term= '''[[dominance (ecology)|dominance species]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A species which characterizes and dominates an [[ecological community]] as measured by its [[primary productivity]] or [[biomass]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[duck weed]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= }}

{{glossary end}}
