{{defn|defn= }}

{{term|term= '''[[estuary]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A body of [[coast]]al water, attached to both ocean and river, often coloured black as a result of [[silt]] and [[sediment]] being carried by the latter.}}

<span id="ethology"></span>{{term|term= '''[[ethology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The study of animal behavior.}}

{{term|term= '''[[eutrophication]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= An increase in natural or chemical nutrients in an ecosystem. This increase of nutrients typically stimulates growth of some aggressive plant species, thereby hampering that of others, and harming [[biodiversity]]. In aquatic ecosystems, it may result in [[hypoxia (environmental)|hypoxia]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[evaporation]]'''}}
{{defn|defn=  the slow [[vaporization]] of water from either the soil o from [[surface water]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[evolutionary ecology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= (or [[ecoevolution]]) the [[evolution]]ary changes occurring to an organism within its population or within the wider [[community (ecology)|community]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[exotic species]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= An introduced species not native or [[endemic]] to a habitat.}}

<span id="extinction"></span>{{term|term= '''[[extinction]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The termination of an organism or of a [[taxon]], usually a species, which occurs when the [[endling|last individual organism]] of the taxon dies. Compare [[#functional extinction|functional extinction]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[extinction vortex]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= }}

{{term|term= '''[[extreme environment]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= An environment in which few living organisms can survive.}}

{{term|term= '''[[extremophile]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= An organism which thrives in physically or [[geochemistry|geochemically]] extreme conditions.}}

{{glossary end}}
