==F==

{{glossary}}
{{term|term= '''[[bottom water#Lake hydrography|fall overturn]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The mixing (or "turning over") of lake water occurring in [[autumn]], facilitating its [[oxygenation (environmental)|re-oxygenation]].}}

<span id="fire ecology"></span>{{term|term= '''[[fire ecology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A branch of ecology which studies the ecological role of naturally occurring [[wildfires]].}}

<span id="fixed action pattern"></span>{{term|term= '''[[fixed action pattern]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= In [[ethology]], an instinctive behaviorial pattern.}}

<span id="flagship species"></span>{{term|term= '''[[flagship species]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A species chosen to represent an environmental cause, such as an ecosystem in need of conservation.}}

<span id="food chain"></span>{{term|term= '''[[food chain]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A group of organisms interrelated by the fact that each member of the group feeds upon the one below it.}}

{{term|term= '''food density'''}}
{{defn|defn= The amount of food available within a given [[#ecotope|ecotope]].}}

<span id="food web"></span>{{term|term= '''[[food web]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A set of interconnected [[food chain]]s by which energy and nutrients circulate within an ecosystem.}}

{{term|term= '''[[forest ecology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A branch of ecology that studies the interrelated patterns, processes, flora, fauna, and ecosystems within [[forest]]s.}}

{{term|term= '''[[foundation species]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A species that is a [[dominant species (ecology)|dominant]] [[primary producer]] in its ecosystem, both in terms of abundance and influence on other organisms and the environment.}}

{{term|term= '''[[founder effect]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The accumulation of random genetic changes in an isolated population.}}

{{term|term= '''[[freshwater biology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= }}

{{term|term= '''[[functional ecology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A branch of ecology which studies the roles, or functions, that certain species (or groups of species) play in an ecosystem.}}

<span id="functional extinction"></span>{{term|term= '''[[functional extinction]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The [[#extinction|extinction]] of a species or other [[taxon]] such that reports of its existence cease, the reduced population no longer plays a significant role in ecosystem function, or the population is no longer viable because it is unable to sustain healthy reproduction.}}

{{term|term= '''[[functional response]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The intake rate of a [[heterotroph|consumer]] as a [[function (mathematics)|function]] of food density.}}

{{term|term= '''[[fungus]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Along with [[bacteria]], fungi are the major [[#decomposer|decomposer]]s in most terrestrial (and some aquatic) ecosystems and therefore play a crucial role in the [[#nutrient cycle|nutrient cycle]].}}

{{glossary end}}
