==I==

{{glossary}}
{{term|term= '''[[illegitimate receivers|illegitimate receiver]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= An organism that intercepts a signal intended for another organism, to the [[fitness (biology)|fitness]] detriment of either the signaler or the legitimate receiver of the signal.}}

<span id="indicator species"></span>{{term|term= '''[[indicator species]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Any living species that defines a trait or characteristic of its environment. The presence and/or abundance of organisms of these species can be used as an indication of the health of a given ecosystem.}}

{{term|term= '''[[instinctive behavior]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The inherent inclination of an organism towards a particular complex behavior.}}

{{term|term= '''[[insular biogeography]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The study of the distributions of biological [[community (ecology)|communities]] on [[island]]s.}}

{{term|term= '''[[intermediate disturbance hypothesis]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A theory that tries to predict how [[species diversity]] will change with varying levels of [[disturbance (ecology)|disturbance]].}}

<span id="interspecific competition"></span>{{term|term= '''[[interspecific competition]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A form of competition that occurs between individuals of different species, e.g. when different species try to use the same [[resource (biology)|resources]] in an environment. Compare with [[#intraspecific competition|intraspecific competition]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[intertidal zone]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A [[coast]]al area periodically submerged underwater by the action of [[tide]]s.}}

{{term|term= '''[[intraspecific competition]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A form of competition that occurs between individuals of the same species, e.g. when members of the same species compete for territories or access to mates. Compare with [[#interspecific competition|interspecific competition]].}}

<span id="invasive species"></span>{{term|term= '''[[invasive species]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A [[indigenous (ecology)|non-native]] species whose introduction to an area causes economic or environmental harm or harm to human health.}}

{{term|term= '''[[ion exchange]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A reversible [[chemical reaction]] where [[ion]]s with the same charge are switched. This principle is used in the purification of waste water.}}

{{glossary end}}
