==M==

{{glossary}}
<span id="macroecology"></span>{{term|term= '''[[macroecology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A branch of ecology which examines ecological phenomena at the largest possible scale. Compare with [[#microecology|microecology]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[mangrove|mangrove wetland]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Mangroves are [[shrub]]s or small trees that grow in coastal [[saline water|saline]] or [[brackish water]] in the [[tropics]] and provide a habitat to many [[marine organism]]s.}}

{{term|term= '''[[marine ecosystem]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= An aquatic ecosystem dominated and defined by the presence of [[saline water]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[marine snow]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= Tiny particles, including dead organic matter from the upper layers of the ocean, sinking deep into the ocean.}}

{{term|term= '''[[mark and recapture]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= An observational methodology used to estimate variables of a population under study, including population density, survival rates, movement, and growth.}}

{{term|term= '''[[marsh]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A wetland dominated by herbaceous rather than woody plant species and often found at the edges of lakes and streams, where it forms a transition between the aquatic and terrestrial ecosystems.}}

{{term|term= '''[[mesopredator release hypothesis]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A hypothesis which states that as [[top predator]]s dwindle in an ecosystem, an increase in the different populations of [[mesopredator]]s occurs.}}

{{term|term= '''[[metabolic theory of ecology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A theory that explains the relationship between an organism's body mass and [[metabolic rate]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[microbial ecology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A branch of ecology that studies [[microorganism]]s.}}

{{term|term= '''[[micro-climate]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A local set of [[atmosphere of Earth|atmospheric conditions]] that differ from those in surrounding areas.}}

<span id="microecology"></span>{{term|term= '''[[microecology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A branch of ecology which studies ecological phenomena at very small scales. Compare with [[#macroecology|macroecology]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[wiktionary:migration|migration]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The movement of organisms from one place to another.}}

{{term|term= '''[[mimicry]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= An adaptive similarity of one species to another that protects one or both species from predators.}}

<span id="molecular ecology"></span>{{term|term= '''[[molecular ecology]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A branch of ecology concerned with applying molecular [[population genetics]], [[molecular phylogenetics]], and [[genomics]] to traditional ecological questions. It is essentially the same as [[ecological genetics]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[monsoon]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The predictable occurrence of dramatic seasonal changes in atmospheric circulation and [[precipitation]] patterns.}}

{{term|term= '''[[mutualism (biology)|mutualism]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A form of [[symbiosis]] from which both individual organisms involved derive a [[fitness (biology)|fitness]] benefit.}}

{{glossary end}}
{{compact ToC|side=yes|center=yes|nobreak=yes|seealso=yes|refs=yes|extlinks=yes|}}

