<span id="negative feedback loop"></span>{{term|term= '''[[negative feedback loop]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A process in which the effects of a change in a system act to reduce or counteract the change. Negative feedback loops tend to promote stability and a settling to [[list of types of equilibrium|equilibrium]], reducing the effects of perturbations in the system. Compare [[#positive feedback loop|positive feedback loop]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[Neutral theory of molecular evolution|neutralism]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The belief that changes in [[evolution]] are caused by random mutation rather than by [[natural selection]].}}

