<span id="nitrogen cycle"></span>{{term|term= '''[[nitrogen cycle]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The continuous cycle by which atmospheric [[nitrogen]] and [[chemical compound|compounded nitrogen]] are continually exchanged through the soil into substances that can be taken up and used by green plants; what is left returns to the atmosphere as a result of [[#denitrification|denitrification]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[nitrogen fixation]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The conversion of [[nitrogen]] into nitrogen compounds (ex. [[nitrate]], [[nitrite]]) that is carried out naturally by certain [[bacteria]] and [[algae]].}}

{{term|term= '''[[numerical response]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= A change in [[predator]] density as a [[function (mathematics)|function]] of change in [[prey]] density.}}

<span id="nutrient"></span>{{term|term= '''[[nutrient]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= [[Chemical element]]s and [[chemical compound|compounds]] that provide organisms with the necessary [[nutrition|nourishment]].}}

<span id="nutrient cycle"></span>{{term|term= '''[[nutrient cycle]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= The movement and exchange of [[organic matter|organic]] and inorganic matter back into the [[productivity (ecology)|production]] of living matter. Also called ''ecological recycling''.}}

{{term|term= '''[[ecosystem ecology|nutrient cycle efficiency]]'''}}
{{defn|defn= See [[#ecosystem ecology|ecosystem ecology]].}}

