{{Infobox journal | title = International Journal of Remote Sensing | image = <!-- or |cover= --> | image_size = | alt = | caption = | former_name = | abbreviation = Int. J. Remote Sens. | bluebook = <!-- For law journals only --> | discipline = [[Geography]] | peer-reviewed = | language = English | editors = Timothy A. Warner, Arthur P. Cracknell | publisher = [[Taylor & Francis]] | country = | history = 1980-present | frequency = Semimonthly | openaccess = | license = | impact = 1.724 | impact-year = 2016 | ISSNlabel = | ISSN = 0143-1161 | eISSN = | CODEN = IJSEDK | JSTOR = | LCCN = 81649524 | OCLC = | website = https://www.tandfonline.com/toc/tres20/current | link1 = https://www.tandfonline.com/toc/tres20/current?nav=tocList | link1-name = Online access | link2 = https://www.tandfonline.com/loi/tres20 | link2-name = Online archive | boxwidth = }} The '''''International Journal of Remote Sensing''''' is a semimonthly [[peer-review]]ed [[scientific journal]] covering research on [[remote sensing]]. It was established in 1980 and is published by [[Taylor & Francis]] on behalf of the [[Remote Sensing and Photogrammetry Society]], of which it is the official journal. The journal '''''Remote Sensing Reviews''''', which was established in 1983, was incorporated into the ''International Journal of Remote Sensing'' in 2001. The [[editors-in-chief]] are Timothy A. Warner ([[West Virginia University]]) and Arthur P. Cracknell ([[University of Dundee]]). According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has a 2016 [[impact factor]] of 1.724.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2017 |chapter=International Journal of Remote Sensing |title=2016 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Clarivate Analytics]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]]}}</ref>
