{{Infobox Lunar mare
|name        = Sinus Roris
|image       = [[Image:Sinus-roris-clem1.jpg|200px|Sinus Roris]]
|caption     = 
|coordinates = {{coord|54.0|N|56.6|W|globe:moon_type:landmark|display=inline,title}}
|diameter    = 202 km
|eponym      = Bay of Dew
}}
'''Sinus Roris''' ([[Latin]] for "Bay of Dew") is an extension of the northern edge of [[Oceanus Procellarum]] on the [[Moon]]. The [[International Astronomical Union|IAU]]-defined [[selenographic coordinates]] of this bay are 54.0° N, 56.6° W, and the diameter is 202&nbsp;km.

The borders of this feature are somewhat indistinct. The bay proper is framed along the western edge by the craters [[Markov (crater)|Markov]] and [[Oenopides (crater)|Oenopides]], and to the north by [[Babbage (crater)|Babbage]] and [[South (lunar crater)|South]]. At the eastern edge it joins the [[Mare Frigoris]].

Many [[Selenography|selenographers]] have taken liberties with the dimensions of Sinus Roris. Lunar maps often indicate a much larger region for this bay than the official dimensions. These can range out as far as the craters [[Gerard (crater)|Gerard]] and [[Repsold (crater)|Repsold]] to the west, [[Harpalus (crater)|Harpalus]] to the east, and as far south as 44° N [[latitude]], approaching [[Mons Rümker]].

The area where the official coordinates place this bay has a generally higher [[albedo]] than the mare to the south, most likely due to deposits of ejecta from impacts to the north.

Early concepts of a moon landing promoted by [[Wernher von Braun]] envisaged the establishment of a permanent lunar base in the Sinus Roris region.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.astronautix.com/craft/vonander.htm |title=Von Braun Lunar Lander |publisher=Encyclopedia Astronautica |accessdate=September 5, 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150824110143/http://www.astronautix.com/craft/vonander.htm |archivedate=August 24, 2015 |df= }}</ref> These concepts lead, in much modified form, to [[Project Apollo]].

[[Arthur C. Clarke]]'s novel ''[[A Fall of Moondust]]'' is set in a fictional "Sea of Thirst" located within Sinus Roris.

